<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="34" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="1" pageNumber="34">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="1" pageNumber="34">
Based on material from Taiwan, this species has recently been redescribed and illustrated in due detail (
<bibRefCitation author="Golovatch, SI" journalOrPublisher="Tropical Natural History" pageId="8" pageNumber="41" pagination="119 - 134" title="The millipede families Cryptodesmidae, Haplodesmidae, Pyrgodesmidae, Opisotretidae and Xystodesmidae in Taiwan (Diplopoda, Polydesmida)." volume="11" year="2011">Golovatch et al. 2011</bibRefCitation>
). It is common in southern Japan and Taiwan (
<bibRefCitation author="Golovatch, SI" journalOrPublisher="Tropical Natural History" pageId="8" pageNumber="41" pagination="119 - 134" title="The millipede families Cryptodesmidae, Haplodesmidae, Pyrgodesmidae, Opisotretidae and Xystodesmidae in Taiwan (Diplopoda, Polydesmida)." volume="11" year="2011">Golovatch et al. 2011</bibRefCitation>
), erroneously reported also from continental China (
<bibRefCitation author="Golovatch, SI" journalOrPublisher="Arthropoda Selecta" pageId="8" pageNumber="41" pagination="129 - 143" title="New or poorly-known millipedes (Diplopoda) from Papua New Guinea, 2." volume="19" year="2010">Golovatch et al. 2010</bibRefCitation>
). The Vietnamese samples fully agree with the detailed account given by 
<bibRefCitation author="Golovatch, SI" journalOrPublisher="Tropical Natural History" pageId="8" pageNumber="41" pagination="119 - 134" title="The millipede families Cryptodesmidae, Haplodesmidae, Pyrgodesmidae, Opisotretidae and Xystodesmidae in Taiwan (Diplopoda, Polydesmida)." volume="11" year="2011">Golovatch et al. (2011)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
